  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Jamieson-Fausset-Brown Bible Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "28. With a great sum obtained I this freedom—Roman citizenship was bought and sold in the reign of Claudius, we know, at a high price: at a subsequent date, for next to nothing. But to put in a false claim to this privilege was a capital crime.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "I was free born—born to it, by purchase, or in reward of services, on the part of his father or some ancestor.",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
